  "title": "Architectural Manager (Construction)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job description</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead site coordination for Architectural trades, collaborate and communicate effectively with architectural services and other trades on-site</li>\n  <li>Manage architectural work scheduling, material procurement, cost control, project oversight, and documentation.</li>\n  <li>Assist in the implementation, monitoring, and review of a construction management plan, supervise and inspect all architectural work performed by subcontractors.</li>\n  <li>Support the Project Manager in all coordination work of civil, structural, architectural and System-Wide Contractors (SWCs)</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with architectural specifications and achieve quality aspect of architectural works without deviation to authority requirements</li>\n  <li>Prepare and coordinate on quality management and CONQUAS assessment</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Architectural or related discipline recognized by BOA.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 5-7 years’ of relevant experience.</li>\n  <li>Able to lead the sub-contractors to ensure smooth progress of works, high quality standards and minimal defects.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Bayes provides career opportunities with reputable and progressive Employers and prioritizes the interests of all whom we represent. If the role resonates with you and your professional experience complements the responsibilities listed, send your resume to <a href=\"mailto:koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>noel.tan@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></a></p>\n<p><br>\n<strong>Noel TAN (Ms.) | Senior Partner</strong></p>\n<p>Lead, Infrastructures Practice</p>\n<p>EA Registration R2197948</p>",
